articles.description: Bakari Evelyn scored 22 points with four 3-pointers, Max Joseph had 10 of his 12 points in the second half and Valparaiso beat short-handed Illinois State 74-58 on Sunday.
articles.headline: Valparaiso beats short-handed Valparaiso 74-58

articles.description: Lucas Siewert scored a career-high 17 points, including a pair of 3-pointers down the stretch, and the Colorado Buffaloes beat the Stanford Cardinal 64-56 Sunday for their third win in a row.
articles.headline: Buffs win third straight as Colorado downs Stanford 64-56

articles.description: Kavion Pippen scored 21 points with eight rebounds and four blocks and Southern Illinois defeated Bradley 74-57 on Sunday to take over sole possession of second place in the Missouri Valley Conference.
articles.headline: Southern Illinois alone in 2nd in MVC after win over Bradley

articles.description: Upset Saturday in the Big 12 saw four of the league's top five teams lose. No. 19 West Virginia must shake the sting of blowing a late six-point lead at home against Oklahoma State.
articles.headline: No. 19 West Virginia looking to bounce back vs. TCU

articles.description: Bearcats senior Kyle Washington drops 17 points and leads Cincinnati to a 76-51 win over SMU, extending Cincy's perfect streak in the American Athletic Conference.
articles.headline: Cincinnati gets road win over SMU

images.caption: Bearcats senior Kyle Washington drops 17 points and leads Cincinnati to a 76-51 win over SMU, extending Cincy's perfect streak in the American Athletic Conference.
images.name: Cincinnati gets road win over SMU

articles.description: Kyle Washington had 17 points with eight rebounds and No. 6 Cincinnati remained undefeated in American Athletic Conference play, stretching its overall winning streak to 16 games with a 76-51 victory over short-handed SMU on Sunday.
articles.headline: No. 6 Cincinnati routs short-handed SMU for 16th win in row

videos.description: After a bad missed shot attempt, Tulsa's Junior Etou jumps and grabs his own miss then puts the moves on Wichita State defenders and completes the one-handed layup while getting fouled.
videos.headline: Tulsa's Etou hits the one-handed and-1

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Tulsa's Etou hits the one-handed and-1) 2018/01/28 ESHEET

videos.description: Wichita State's Austin Reaves went 7-of-8 in the first half from three and would contribute 23 of the Shockers' 45 first-half points.
videos.headline: Reaves's hot hand keeps Wichita State in contention

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Reaves's hot hand keeps Wichita State in contention) 2018/01/28 ESHEET

videos.description: After a missed shot attempt by teammate Markis McDuffie, Shaquille Morris leaps over Tulsa defenders to deliver a monster 2-handed slam to tie the game at 27-27 for the Shockers.
videos.headline: Morris's monster slam ties the game for Wichita State

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Morris's monster slam ties the game for Wichita State) 2018/01/28 ESHEET

videos.description: Wichita State's Zach Brown finds teammate Shaquille Morris who powers through Tulsa defenders for the dunk to help extend the Shockers lead 68-62.
videos.headline: Morris shreds Tulsa defenders for the slam

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Morris shreds Tulsa defenders for the slam) 2018/01/28 ESHEET

videos.description: Austin Reaves drops 23 points off the bench in an effort to lead No. 17 Wichita State to a 90-71 win over Tulsa.
videos.headline: Reaves powers Shockers to win
